The paper discusses the connection between computational social choice and computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on the use of complexity classification in comsoc suggests that it is most likely to belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mention of benefits to complexity arising from its use in comsoc suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are closely related to computational complexity. Finally, the mention of less-known complexity tools suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which often involves the use of advanced mathematical tools.
